commit.message:
Do not emit error if there is no $HOME environment variable

Using eix in a systemd unit would display this error message on every
invocation of eix. This commit removes the "no $HOME" error message,
as it is largely unnecessary and hence mostly causes noise.
Make contrib/check_includes.sh happy again
Deal with duplicate entries in IUSE, https://github.com/vaeth/eix/issues/88
Fix segfault when reading dependencies of installed versions
Add idepend to hashing, fixing https://github.com/vaeth/eix/issues/87
Add some gcc-11 flags
Use natural order for USE, see https://github.com/vaeth/eix/issues/86
Support idepend. TODO: optimize output
Fix wrong braces configure.ac
Fix --proto category output: https://github.com/vaeth/eix/issues/80
